<li>
<b><a name="faq3">What is the different between mindfulness and meditation??</a></b>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<a href="#top">Back to Top</a>

<p> 
Formal meditation often involves sitting and focusing on a specific object of attention, such as the breath.
Mindfulness involves paying attention to what is going on around you with all of your senses. Therefore, the two words are
not synonyms.

They are often associated with each other, however, as meditation is a good way to prepare to become mindful. Meditation 
quiets the 
inner dialogue that pulls one out of the present and into ruminations about the past or anxieties about the future.
Therefore, at the conclusion of a meditation, one typically emerges in a mindful state that is naturally focused on the present
with acceptance and equanimity.

Mindfulness is like taking that meditative state with you as you go about your business, but not so deeply that it interferes 
with your ability to go about your business. In fact, by helping you cultivate your attention, mindfulness can
help you become more productive.

</li>

