<li>
<b><a name="faq4">Who created <em>Seeing the Roses</em>?</a></b>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
<a href="#top">Back to Top</a>

<p>
The <em>Seeing the Roses</em> project was created by

<a href="http://transparenteye.net/?page_id=387">Rick Heller</a>
 with the help of others among the <a href="http://harvardhumanist.org/">Harvard Humanist</a>
and the <a href="http://www.meetup.com/Cambridge-Secular-Buddhists/">Cambridge-Somerville Secular Buddhist</a> communities.
Rick had been thinking about how mindfulness could  be helpful in dealing with climate change, and was inspired to take it further after hearing
a talk at the <a href="http://www.cimc.info/">Cambridge Insight Meditation Center</a> by Andrew Olendzki on how desire drives climate change. 
Although influenced by Buddhism, <em>Seeing the Roses</em> is a secular practice of cultivating attention that is suitable for people of any or no religious faith.
</p>

</li>

